title: PPPP’s Ikram-Ullah Khan wins PS-22 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarians’ (PPPP) Ikram- Ullah Khan has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-22, Sukkur -1 by securing 41,828 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Muhammad Mubeen of Jamiat ulema e Islam Pakistan, who bagged votes 39,778.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 48.78 %.
